1
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:56,400
<i>She looks at me every day.</i>

2
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:58,280
<i>Mary Jane Watson.</i>

3
00:02:58,440 --> 00:03:02,320
<i>Oh, boy. If she only knew
how I felt about her.</i>

4
00:03:02,480 --> 00:03:04,200
<i>But she can never know.</i>

5
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:07,640
<i>I made a choice once to live
a life of responsibility.</i>

6
00:03:07,800 --> 00:03:10,000
<i>A life she can never be a part of.</i>

7
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,440
<i>Who am I?</i>

8
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:14,080
<i>I'm Spider-Man, given a job to do.</i>

9
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:17,120
<i>And I'm Peter Parker,
and I, too, have a job.</i>

10
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,800
Parker. Parker!

11
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:21,080
No, no, no, stop! Stop!

12
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:25,040
Parker, you're late, man. Always late.

13
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:28,000
I'm sorry, Mr. Aziz.
There was a disturbance.

14
00:03:28,160 --> 00:03:30,320
Another disturbance.
Always a disturbance with you.

15
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:33,200
Come on, 21 minutes ago,
in comes order.

16
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:37,480
Harmattan, Burton & Smith.
Eight extra-large deep-dish pizzas.

17
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,600
I told you,
I don't understand that language.

18
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:42,640
- Speak English.
- You can't make pizza.

19
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:44,560
I can't?
I've been making pizza five years.

20
00:03:44,760 --> 00:03:47,440
In eight minutes, I am defaulting on
Joe's 29-minute guarantee.

21
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:50,400
Then, not only am I receiving
no money for these pizzas...

22
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:53,080
...but I will lose the customer forever
to Pizza Yurt.

23
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:56,320
- Why didn't you send Saleem?
- Saleem was deported yesterday.

24
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:58,400
- Look... Smiley.
- What about my cheese pizza?

25
00:03:58,560 --> 00:04:01,440
Look, you are my only hope, all right?
You have to make it in time.

26
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:05,560
Peter, you're a nice guy.
But you're just not dependable.

27
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,720
This is your last chance.

28
00:04:07,880 --> 00:04:12,400
You have to go 42 blocks
in 7 1/2 minutes or your ass is fired.

29
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,840
Go!

30
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,520
Hey, what, are you stupid?

31
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:02,680
Whoa! He stole that guy's pizzas!

32
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:12,560
I'm gonna get it!

33
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,800
Hey, you guys.
No playing in the streets.

34
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:31,160
Yes, Mr. Spider-Man.

35
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,040
See you.

36
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,280
Way to go, Spidey!

37
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,520
Pizza time.

38
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:49,600
You're late.

39
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,760
I'm not paying for those.

40
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:11,680
Elevator.

41
00:07:27,800 --> 00:07:31,160
Joe's 29-minute guarantee
is a promise, man.

42
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:35,640
I know to you, Parker, a promise
means nothing. But to me, it's serious.

43
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,720
It's serious to me too, Mr. Aziz.

44
00:07:37,880 --> 00:07:40,240
- You're fired. Go.
- Please, I need this job.

45
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:42,840
- You're fired.
- Look, give me another chance.

46
00:07:51,640 --> 00:07:52,920
<i>You're fired.</i>

47
00:07:53,280 --> 00:07:55,200
- Parker, hello. You're fired.
- Why?

48
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:56,800
Dogs catching Frisbees?

49
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:59,160
Pigeons in the park?
A couple geezers playing chess?

50
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:00,520
- Boss.
- Not now.

51
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:03,280
<i>The Bugle could show another side
of New York for a change.</i>

52
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:06,280
We got six minutes to deadline, Jonah.
We need page one.

53
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:09,720
I don't pay you to be a sensitive artiste.
I pay you... Still not now!

54
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:12,360
I pay you because that psycho
Spider-Man will pose for you.

55
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:14,160
He won't let me take
any more pictures.

56
00:08:14,360 --> 00:08:15,880
You turned the whole city
against him.

57
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,480
A fact I'm very proud of.

58
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:21,240
Get your pretty little portfolio off my
desk before I go into a diabetic coma.

59
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:24,640
- It's your wife, she lost her checkbook.
- Thanks for the good news.

60
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:28,000
Please, isn't there any of these shots
you can use? I need the money.

61
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:31,080
Miss Brant. Get me a violin.

62
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,880
Five minutes to deadline, Jonah.

63
00:08:33,040 --> 00:08:35,600
Run a picture of a rancid chicken.
Here's the headline:

64
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:37,600
"Food Poisoning Scare Sweeps City."

65
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,960
- Some food got poisoned?
- I'm a little nauseous.

66
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:41,920
All right, Mr. Jameson.

67
00:08:43,560 --> 00:08:45,640
It stinks.
Robbie, there's your page one.

68
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,360
"Masked Menace Terrorizes Town."

69
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:49,040
I told you, he's not a menace.

70
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,720
- I told you...
- I'll take care of it.

71
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,440
- I'll give you 150.
- Three hundred.

72
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,040
That's outrageous.

73
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:56,120
Done. Give this to the girl.

74
00:08:56,280 --> 00:08:57,400
Thank you. Bye-bye.

75
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,280
Hi.

76
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:00,920
Hey, Pete.

77
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:07,440
I don't think this covers the advance
I gave you a couple weeks ago.

78
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:09,640
- Right.
- Sorry.

79
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:11,960
Hey.

80
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,960
Chin up, okay?

81
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,960
Watch it, jerk!

82
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,080
Dr. Connors. Sorry.

83
00:09:40,240 --> 00:09:41,680
Where were you headed, Parker?

84
00:09:41,920 --> 00:09:43,120
To your class.

85
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:45,040
My class is over.

86
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:47,280
See me standing here?

87
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:51,120
I'm sorry. I'm trying.
I wanna be here.

88
00:09:51,280 --> 00:09:52,560
Then be here.

89
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,280
Look at you, Peter.

90
00:09:55,800 --> 00:09:59,920
Your grades have been steadily
declining. You're late for class.

91
00:10:00,120 --> 00:10:02,880
You always appear exhausted.

92
00:10:04,280 --> 00:10:06,240
Your paper on fusion is still overdue.

93
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:09,440
I know. I'm planning to write it
on Dr. Otto Octavius.

94
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:12,600
Planning is not a major
at this university.

95
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,720
Octavius is a friend of mine.

96
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:19,960
Better do your research, Parker.

97
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:23,320
Get it done, or I'm failing you.

98
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,880
Surprise!

99
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,920
Well, say something.

100
00:10:48,080 --> 00:10:49,280
What's the occasion?

101
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:51,920
Really, Peter. It's your birthday!

102
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:55,120
Whether you want
to remember it or not.

103
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:58,640
He lives in another reality.
Don't you, Pete?

104
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,640
- Hi, M.J.
- Hi.

105
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:02,440
- Hey, buddy.
- Hey.

106
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,760
Long time, no see.

107
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:07,640
So how's the play?
I read a great review.

108
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,440
It's going fine. It's going good.

109
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,800
She's brilliant in it.

110
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,560
Harry sent me roses.

111
00:11:12,760 --> 00:11:15,200
So where you been, pal?
You don't return my calls.

112
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,400
I've been busy.

113
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:22,000
Taking pictures of Spider-Man?
How's the bug these days?

114
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:24,040
The less you see of that man,
the better.

115
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:27,520
Now, let's all go into the other room
and have something to eat.

116
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:28,880
I'll get the hors d'oeuvres.

117
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:31,120
So how are things going at Oscorp?

118
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:34,000
They're great.
I'm head of Special Projects.

119
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:36,320
We're about to make
a breakthrough on fusion.

120
00:11:36,480 --> 00:11:40,400
How lovely, Harry. Your father
would be so proud, rest his soul.

121
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,840
Thank you.

122
00:11:42,200 --> 00:11:45,840
We're actually funding
one of your idols, Pete. Otto Octavius.

123
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:48,320
- I'm writing a paper on him.
- You want to meet him?

124
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,680
You'd introduce me?

125
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:52,920
You bet. Octavius is
gonna put Oscorp on the map...

126
00:11:53,080 --> 00:11:55,040
...in a way my father
never even dreamed of.

127
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,080
M.J., could you give me a hand?

128
00:11:59,320 --> 00:12:00,880
She's waiting for you, pal.

129
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:02,720
What do you mean?

130
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:05,240
The way she looks at you
or doesn't look at you.

131
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:07,080
However you want to look at it.

132
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:09,520
I don't have time for girls right now.

133
00:12:09,680 --> 00:12:10,960
Why, are you dead?

134
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,640
I've been kind of busy.

135
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,320
Taking pictures of your friend?

136
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:17,200
Could we get off that subject?

137
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:20,560
I want us to be friends, Harry.
I want us to trust each other.

138
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:22,320
Then be honest with me.

139
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:25,360
If you knew who he was,
would you tell me?

140
00:12:29,960 --> 00:12:32,240
Peter, don't you understand
how I feel?

141
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:34,240
I want this guy dead.

142
00:12:34,400 --> 00:12:37,080
The same way you want the guy
who killed your Uncle Ben dead.

143
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:47,640
I'm sorry. I don't mean to
rag on you on your birthday.

144
00:12:49,720 --> 00:12:51,640
You're my buddy, you know that.

145
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,800
You're family, Pete.

146
00:12:55,640 --> 00:12:58,920
My father loved you.
You were like a son to him.

147
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:06,400
Thank you, Harry.

148
00:13:38,840 --> 00:13:40,240
May.

149
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:41,920
Oh, what, Ben?

150
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:45,080
Wait.

151
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:46,640
- Aunt May.
- Oh, my.

152
00:13:47,040 --> 00:13:52,040
Oh, Peter. Oh, for a second there,
I thought I was years ago.

153
00:13:54,160 --> 00:13:56,000
Everybody's gone, aren't they?

154
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,000
Did they have a good time?

155
00:13:58,520 --> 00:13:59,720
I'm sure they did.

156
00:14:01,480 --> 00:14:05,160
- You okay?
- Of course. But you go home.

157
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:10,680
And be careful. I don't like that
scooter thing you drive around.

158
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:12,560
I'm worried about you.

159
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:17,760
You're so alone.
And I saw the letter from the bank.

160
00:14:17,920 --> 00:14:20,280
Oh, my. You did?

161
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,000
Oh, well.

162
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,560
So?

163
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,680
I'm a little behind.

164
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,280
Everybody is.

165
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:31,800
Anyway, I don't want
to talk about it anymore.

166
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:35,560
I'm tired,
and you better start back home.

167
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:39,680
Here, kiddo. Happy birthday.

168
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,560
You need it more than I do.

169
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:44,160
- No, I can't take that from you.
- Yes, you can!

170
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:46,280
You can take this money from me.

171
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:49,040
For God's sake, it's not much.
Now, take it!

172
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:51,600
And don't you dare leave it here.

173
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,640
Oh, I'm sorry.

174
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:58,160
It's just that I miss
your uncle Ben so much.

175
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:04,960
Can you believe that it's two years
next month since he was taken?

176
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,320
I think to myself at times...

177
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:14,560
...were I to face the one responsible
for what happened, I'd...

178
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,520
Oh, I don't know what I'd do.

179
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:25,320
Now...

180
00:15:27,160 --> 00:15:29,760
...you better take
the rest of your cake home.

181
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,320
Hey.

182
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:47,520
Hey. You're still here.

183
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,160
I saw your billboard on Bleecker.

184
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:53,520
Isn't it funny?
I'm really kind of embarrassed.

185
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:57,480
Don't be. It's nice.
I get to see you every day now.

186
00:15:57,680 --> 00:15:59,000
The photographer liked my face.

187
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:01,920
I was only supposed to be
in the catalogue.

188
00:16:02,080 --> 00:16:05,440
Then I got the part in the play.
Everything at once.

189
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,520
Your dream came true.

190
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:09,760
How about yours?

191
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:14,640
I'm fine.

192
00:16:16,640 --> 00:16:18,920
I wish you'd come see the play.

193
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:21,200
You're the one who
always encouraged me.

194
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,800
I plan to.

195
00:16:28,640 --> 00:16:30,880
I liked seeing you tonight, Peter.

196
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,720
Oh, boy, yeah.

197
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:38,160
"Oh, boy, yeah" what?

198
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:44,080
Nothing.

199
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:50,040
Do you want to say something?

200
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:57,320
I...

201
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,240
...was...

202
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:08,320
...wondering if you're still
in the Village.

203
00:17:17,080 --> 00:17:19,040
You're such a mystery.

204
00:17:28,880 --> 00:17:30,600
Peter.

205
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:33,400
What?

206
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,840
Happy birthday.

207
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:50,240
I'm seeing somebody now.

208
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:54,160
- Therapy.
- No.

209
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:56,080
A person, a man.

210
00:17:56,240 --> 00:17:58,480
You mean, like a boyfriend?

211
00:17:58,680 --> 00:18:01,200
Well, like I like him.

212
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:05,600
What?

213
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:07,880
Nothing.

214
00:18:08,720 --> 00:18:11,800
That's good, you know?
Companionship...

215
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:15,040
May be more than that.

216
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:17,560
More?

217
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:19,680
I don't know.

218
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:23,120
I'm coming to see your play
tomorrow night.

219
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:28,880
- You're coming?
- I'll be there.

220
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:31,440
Don't disappoint me.

221
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:34,400
I won't.

222
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:49,480
Rent.

223
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:55,760
- Hi.
- Hi. What's "hi"?

224
00:18:55,920 --> 00:18:57,360
Can I spend it?

225
00:18:58,080 --> 00:18:59,920
I have a paycheck due this week
and...

226
00:19:00,080 --> 00:19:03,280
- You're a month late again. Again.
- I promise as soon as...

227
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:06,760
If promises were crackers,
my daughter would be fat.

228
00:19:07,360 --> 00:19:11,640
I'm really sorry, Mr. Ditkovitch. All I got
is this 20 for the rest of the week.

229
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:13,840
"Sorry" doesn't pay the rent.

230
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:18,640
And don't try to sneak past me. I have
ears like a cat and eyes like a rodent.

231
00:19:20,280 --> 00:19:23,000
- Thanks, Mr. Ditkovitch.
- Hi, Pete.

232
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,200
Hello?

233
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,880
Rent?

234
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:32,080
Doctor? Mr. Osborn's here.

235
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:36,040
Nobel Prize, Otto. Nobel Prize.
And we'll all be rich.

236
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:37,800
It's not about the prizes, Harry.

237
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:39,680
But you need money.
You need Oscorp.

238
00:20:39,840 --> 00:20:41,040
Who do we have here?

239
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,840
This is my good friend
I called you about.

240
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,600
He got me through
high-school science.

241
00:20:44,760 --> 00:20:47,720
Peter Parker, sir.
I'm writing a paper on you for...

242
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:49,240
I know what you're doing here...

243
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:51,520
...but I don't have time
to talk to students now.

244
00:20:52,440 --> 00:20:54,200
But Oscorp pays the bills, so...

245
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:56,600
That's why I have to take off.
Board meeting.

246
00:20:56,760 --> 00:21:00,000
But my job is done here.
Got you two geniuses together.

247
00:21:00,160 --> 00:21:04,560
Good luck tomorrow, Otto.
Nobel Prize. We'll see you in Sweden!

248
00:21:07,160 --> 00:21:08,600
Interesting fellow, your friend.

249
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,840
I won't take much of your time.

250
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:15,160
Now I remember you. You're Connors'
student. He tells me you're brilliant.

251
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:17,960
He also tells me you're lazy.

252
00:21:18,920 --> 00:21:20,080
I'm trying to do better.

